{{Infobox organization |name = International Union of Geodesy and Geophysics |image = International Union of Geodesy and Geophysics logo.jpeg |image_border = |size = 150 |alt = green, dark blue, and white design within a circle |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = IUGG |motto = |formation = {{start date and age|1919}} |extinction = |type = [[International nongovernmental organization|INGO]] |status = |purpose = |headquarters = |location = Potsdam, Germany |region_served = Worldwide |membership = |language = English, French |leader_title = President |leader_name = Michael Sideris (Canada) |leader_title2 = Vice President |leader_name2 = Kathryn Whaler (UK) |leader_title3 = Secretary General |leader_name3 = Alik Ismail-Zadeh (Germany/Russia) |leader_title4 = Treasurer |leader_name4 = Aksel W. Hansen (Denmark) |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.iugg.org/ IUGG Official website] |remarks = }}
[[File:DBP 1983 1187 Geodäsie und Geophysik.jpg|thumb|upright|German stamp about the IUGG General Assembly in 1983, Hamburg]]
The '''International Union of Geodesy and Geophysics''' ('''IUGG'''; {{lang-fr|Union géodésique et géophysique internationale}}, '''UGGI''') is an [[international non-governmental organisation]] dedicated to the scientific study of the [[Earth]] and its [[space environment]] using [[Geophysics|geophysical]] and [[Geodesy|geodetic]] techniques.
The IUGG was established in Brussels, Belgium in 1919.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Lyons|first1=Henry G.|title=The Brussels Meeting of the International Research Council|journal=Nature|year=1919|volume=103|issue=2598|pages=464–466}}</ref><ref name=Cochrane>{{cite book|last=Cochrane|first=Rexmond C.|title=The National Academy of Sciences: The First Hundred Years, 1863-1963|year=1978|publisher=National Academies}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Good|first1=Gregory A.|title=The Assembly of Geophysics: Scientific Disciplines as Frameworks of Consensus|journal=Studies in History and Philosophy of Science Part B: Studies in History and Philosophy of Modern Physics|year=2000|volume=31|issue=3|pages=259–292|doi=10.1016/S1355-2198(00)00018-6|ref=harv|bibcode=2000SHPMP..31..259G}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Ismail-Zadeh|first1=Alik|title=Geoscience international: the role of scientific unions|journal=Hist. Geo Space Sci.|year=2016|volume=7|pages=103-123}}</ref> Some areas within its scope are environmental preservation, reduction of the effects of natural hazards, and [[mineral]] resources.
== Objectives == IUGG's objectives are the promotion and coordination of studies related to Earth's physical, chemical and mathematical representation. This includes geometrical shape, internal structure, gravity and magnetic fields, [[seismicity]], [[volcanism]], [[hydrologic cycle]], glaciers, oceans, atmosphere, [[ionosphere]], and [[magnetosphere]] of Earth. It also includes solar, lunar and planetary studies.<ref>Burchfiel, B. C. (1987) [https://books.google.com/books?id=Nz0rAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA32 ''International Role of U.S. Geoscience''] US National Academies page 32</ref>
== Structures == The IUGG consists of eight semi-autonomous associations:<ref>{{cite web|title=Associations of the IUGG|url=http://www.iugg.org/associations/|publisher=International Union of Geodesy and Geophysics|accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref> *[[International Association of Cryospheric Sciences]] (IACS) *[[International Association of Geodesy]] (IAG) *[[International Association of Geomagnetism and Aeronomy]] (IAGA) *[[International Association of Hydrological Sciences]] (IAHS) *International Association of Meteorology and Atmospheric Sciences (IAMAS) *International Association for the Physical Sciences of the Oceans (IAPSO) *International Association of Seismology and Physics of the Earth's Interior (IASPEI) *[[International Association of Volcanology and Chemistry of the Earth's Interior]] (IAVCEI)
It has also established six commissions to promote interdisciplinary problems:<ref>{{cite web|title=Union Commissions|url=http://www.iugg.org/about/commissions/|publisher=International Union of Geodesy and Geophysics|accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref> *Climatic and Environmental Changes (CCEC) *Mathematical Geophysics (CMG) *Geophysical Risk and Sustainability (GRC) *Study of the Earth's Deep Interior (SEDI) *Data and Information (UCDI) *Planetary Sciences (UCPS) and the Union Working Group on History.
