{{Refimprove|date=May 2014}} [[File:Zeuxo Chrysippos BM E65.jpg|thumb|right|Zeuxo pours wine to [[Chrysippus (mythology)|Chrysippus]]. Interior from an Attic red-figured kylix, ca. 490-480 BC. From Capua.]]
In [[Greek mythology]] '''Zeuxo''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|zj|uː|k|s|oʊ}}; Ζευξώ) was an [[Oceanid]]. Her name appears in [[Hesiod]]'s catalogue of Oceanid names;<ref>Hesiod, ''[[Theogony]]'', 352</ref> no other literary mention of her survives.
